What a nice guy, he told us each character of the flag is preceded by 6 digits! That make the challenge easy, all we need to do is paste the given text into a text editor, and use some simple regex to extract the flag!

Something like \d{6}. should work. Or you can use this recipe in [Cyberchef](https://gchq.github.io/CyberChef/#recipe=Regular_expression('User%20defined','(?%3C%3D%5B%5E0-9%5D%5B0-9%5D%7B6%7D).',true,true,false,false,false,false,'List%20matches')Remove_whitespace(true,true,true,true,true,false)&input=Pj1pXlNFYzU0bSQ6SkhIQVREbDhII0lnNyQ7WVNSL1Q1UUAvVDVRQC9UNVFAJTE1WEtFY2BGTERmbEtyJTE2PD9BVERqJys%%%%)! Fun fact, if you remove the 6 digits and flag characters, the remaining script can be base85 decoded to reveal a [hidden message](https://gchq.github.io/CyberChef/#recipe=From_Base85('!-u',true,'z')&input=Pj1pXlNFYzU0bSQ6SkhIQVREbDhII0lnNyQ7WVNSL1Q1UUAvVDVRQC9UNVFAJTE1WEtFY2BGTERmbEtyJTE2PD9BVERqJys%%2BOkJsa2Q1JDsjLFZCazFkKytFcUI%%%%%%2BbjxGPEdqSUZUDQoNCg0KCQ&ieol=CRLF&oeol=CRLF)!!!
